start AWS instance
Allow traffic on port 5000
	Go to AWS dashboard.
	search for security groups.
	select your instance and scroll down.
	click on edit.
	add custom TCP rule and select port 5000.
	restart the instance.
	Now, port 5000 can be used for instance.
	
connect to instance using ssh

install python
	sudo apt-get install python
install pip
	sudo apt-get update
	sudo apt-get install python-pip
install flask
	pip install flask
install flask_login
	pip install flask_login
install sqlalchemy
	pip install flask_sqlalchemy
install CORS
	pip install flask_cors
install bcrypt
	pip install flask_bcrypt	
install http request
	pip install request
install pybase64
	pip install pybase64
sudo apt-get update

transfer all files to instance using scp.

The App runs on "0.0.0.0"on port:5000
